citRespParty.rpOrgName: Afghanistan Geodesy and Cartography Head Office (AGCHO)

dataIdInfo.idAbs: The file name for this dataset is "afg_admbnda_adm2_agcho_20180522". The structure of the attribute table and field names have been modified to provide consistent notation across the CODs.

Consts.useLimit: This dataset is strictly for humanitarian purposes.

dataIdInfo.idPurp: This spatial dataset provides the delimitation and composition of the Afghanistan district boundaries and forms one of the Common Operational Datasets (COD) for the humanitarian community. It comprises 399 district boundaries, and is attributed with the AGCHO administrative codes and names (Dari and English).
dataIdInfo.idCredit: Source: Afghanistan Geodesy and Cartography Head Office (AGCHO). AGCHO and the Independent Directorate for Local Governance (IDLG) are recognised as the sole authoritative source for legal and technical issues related to the delimitation of administrative boundaries, composition, and division of the administrative units of Afghanistan as per the following references: 1) Letter between AGCHO and the President's Office (dated 5 March 2007); and 2) Joint statement from IDLG and AGCHO (dated 26 March 2012).

themeKeys.keyword: Common Operational Dataset, COD, Administrative Level 2 Boundaries, District Boundaries, AGCHO

dataLineage.statement:
Layer was sent as a shapefile to ITOS in an email from the IMO. It was then analyzed by ITOS for errors. Those errors were corrected and then the layer was sent back to UNOCHA as a feature class within a file geodatabase.
NOTE: This layer has attribution fields for UNAMA regions, geographic areas used by the humanitarian community that are not an official administrative boundary.
The following errors were found and fixed by ITOS: 1. Admin2 English name "Darwaz-e-Balla" did not have a 1 to 1 relationship to the Dari names. The IMO instructed ITOS to do the following: -Change AF1727 Dawraz-e-Bala to AF1722, Dawraz-e-Payin, Mai Mai, Dawraz, درواز پائین (ما می ) -Change AF1722 Dawraz-e-Bala to AF1727, Dawraz-e-Bala, Nusai, دروازبالا ( نیسی) 2. Admin2 Dari names "دولت آباد", "ریگ", "سروبی", "قره باغ" and "کوهستان" did not have a 1 to 1 relationship to the English names. This is mainly due to the English names having spelling differences. Dari name “ریگ” had 4 different English names, with “Reg” being used in two different fields. The IMO instructed ITOS to do the following: -Change AF2107, Dawlatabad to Dawlat Abad -Change AF1708, Kohestan to Kohistan -Change AF1111, Qarabagh to Qara Bagh -For AF2716, swap AltName1 and AltName2, change Dari name to ریگ ( شگه ) -Change AF3011 Dari spelling to ریگ خان نشین -Change AF1210 Sarobi to Surobi 3. Two Admin2 units with English name "Darwaz-e-Balla" were bordering each other within Admin1 "Badakhshan". They have unique Admin2 p-codes and Dari names. This was fixed with the name change to "Dawraz-e-Payin" (see fix number 1 above)
